Title: Descendants of the Chiral Anomaly
Authors: R. Jackiw
Comments: 8 pages, LaTeX, talk presented at the Dirac Medalist Meeting,
  Trieste, Italy, November 2000
Report-no: MIT-CTP#3051
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Mathematical Physics
\\
  Chern-Simons terms are well-known descendants of chiral anomalies, when the
latter are presented as total derivatives. Here I explain that also
Chern-Simons terms, when defined on a 3-manifold, may be expressed as total
derivatives.
